description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you an adult or paediatric theatre trained practitioner, newly qualified or experienced, looking for a change or new opportunities to progress? Do you want to work in a supportive and efficient team? At the Evelina London Children’s Hospital, we carry out specialised and complex surgery in a small hospital attached to Guy’s and St Thomas’ with links to neo-natal surgery. At Evelina theatres we perform a wide range of elective and emergency procedures: ENT, General, Urology, Renal, Ortho, Spine, Plastics, Cleft, Cochlear, Gastro, Respiratory and many more.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You would get the unique chance to rotate through all the specialities being supported by practice development nurses to drive and enhance your career. With an excellent education offering including in-house courses for anaesthetics, scrub and recovery, we will support your development in an environment where you can flourish.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a highly motivated and driven Theatre Scrub Practitioner to join the &lt;strong&gt;Scrub Team&lt;/strong&gt; at Evelina London Children’s Hospital with a passion for delivering the best possible patient care. With an expansion programme that will see 2 new theatres opening, there has never been a better time for you to join our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As well as wanting to provide the best patient care, we also look after our staff and are able to support the right candidate with a flexible approach to work that encourages a healthy work life balance. However, our scrub team partake in nights, late, weekends and on call to provide a 24 hour 7 days a week emergency service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are keen to make a difference to children and your own career why not find out more or apply now?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date: 29th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews to be conducted on the week commencing the 7th of December 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note that all the interviews will be conducted online via Skype for Business or Microsoft Teams.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
